Java Class 5

If statement

SYNTAX

if (boolean condition) {

} //It has to always be a boolean condition, meaning the statement should always be true or false
=======================
boolean weekend = true;

if (weekend){

System.out.println(It is Java class");
}
String day="Saturday";

if (day.equals("Saturday")) {
System.out.println (It is Java class");
}

int date=3;

if (date=3){
System.out.println ("Today is the third");
}

